5|$|In 1676, {{the area}} <b>was</b> <b>burned</b> down after a fire {{started in the}} wooden Transfiguration Cathedral. With the help of Ivan Savelov, a monk {{who lived in the}} monastery and later became a Patriarch of Moscow, the complex was re{{constructed}}. Two years later, {{with the help of the}} cossack community, the Annunciation Church was constructed near the monastery's hospital.|$|E
